         <abstract>
            <p>Given certain implicit difference approximations to $u_t = a(x)u_{xx} + b(x)u_x + c(x)u$ in the region $- \infty &lt; x &lt; \infty, t \geqq 0$, with a finer $x$-mesh width in the left half-plane than in the right, we consider the stability in the maximum norm of these schemes using several different interface conditions (at $x = 0$). In order to obtain our results, we first prove a stability theorem for certain simple second-order parabolic initial boundary systems on an evenly spaced mesh in the right half-plane alone. By a standard procedure, the first problem is converted into the second one, and solved in this manner.</p>
          </abstract>
